_contact_role", "sentiment": "positive, focused on supplier risk and obligations", "_matched_ai": true, "last_contact_date": "2026-06-16"}, {"name": "Arthur Moes", "risk": "Key purchasing influencer who remained skeptical after demos", "role": "Decision Maker", "email": "arthur.moes@aruplab.com", "title": "Group Manager, Purchasing & Material Planning", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "skeptical; 'doesn't know the struggle'; owns supplier and diversity risk", "_matched_ai": true, "last_contact_date": "2025-10-13"}, {"name": "Robert Stipanovich", "risk": "Interested but was traveling and out for stretches; not the budget owner", "role": "Influencer", "email": "stipanra@aruplab.com", "title": "Sourcing Manager", "_source": "sfdc_contact_role", "sentiment": "engaged; 'sees the vision', probed licensing and financial/ERP integration", "_matched_ai": true, "last_contact_date": "2025-10-13"}]}, "meddpicc": {"metrics": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Zycus Debrief 16 Oct 2025", "Zycus X ARUP CLM Demo 13 Oct 2025", "AIS_Why__c"], "narrative": "Pain is well articulated but never quantified in dollars or hours across the whole call history, a real exposure in a competitive RFP where price and value will be scored. On 16 Oct 2025 Michael Tutton described a fully manual process ('We're just reading it, memorizing, trying to remember what's not there... very manual') and the need to go '7 different places' to manage suppliers and contracts. No cost-of-inaction, cycle-time, or ROI figure has ever been put on the table. Putting a savings model inside the proposal is a ranked move."}, "champion": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Zycus Debrief 16 Oct 2025", "Catch up with Zycus 09 Jan 2026", "SF Next_Step 6/29"], "narrative": "Michael Tutton is a strong, conviction-driven champion who found Zycus himself, openly advocates internally ('Everybody always expects me to say something Zycus' - 09 Jan 2026), and is credited in the Next Step with convincing management to launch the RFP. Ondraya Watkins is a confirmed co-champion focused on supplier risk and obligations. His limits: he admits no prior Zycus experience and forces his own objectivity, and he cannot independently move the skeptical director-level budget owner. Strong at the working level but without power-line access, so making him the economic-buyer broker is the highest-leverage use of his strength."}, "competition": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Zycus Debrief 16 Oct 2025", "Zycus X ARUP CLM Demo 13 Oct 2025", "Catch up with Zycus 09 Jan 2026"], "narrative": "The live threat is incumbent Conga (Salesforce CLM), the tool the RFP exists to test, positioned as 'enhance vs replace' and backed by the director's gap-analysis mandate; do-nothing / enhance-Conga-in-place is the real fallback. Zycus wins on external-counsel Word redlining without portal login, clause library, AI contract discovery and risk scoring, post-contract dashboards, and D365/Merlin AI, the exact gap set Michael cannot close on Conga. Coupa is dormant (a peer-positioning reference only). The wedge is differentiation plus a bundled TCO that exposes the hidden cost of enhancing Conga with separate compare and sign tools."}, "identify_pain": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Zycus Debrief 16 Oct 2025", "Zycus X ARUP CLM Demo 13 Oct 2025"], "narrative": "Specific and owner-attributed: a fully manual CLM run through Salesforce/Conga and Word where the team memorizes clause positions and hunts across 7 systems (Michael Tutton, 16 Oct 2025), and Conga treated as a weak repository ('it's not a very good one, but it is a repository'). Ondraya Watkins owns supplier scorecarding and post-contract risk; Arthur Moes owns supplier and minority/woman-owned business risk. Pain is confirmed and multi-owner; its dollar value is not."}, "paper_process": {"status": "gap", "sources": ["Zycus X ARUP CLM Demo 13 Oct 2025", "SF Next_Step 6/29"], "narrative": "The single biggest close-date blind spot. No MSA, SOW, Order Form, or template has been exchanged and no legal, redline, or InfoSec timeline has been discussed. ARUP signs today through Salesforce/Conga's DocuSign (Michael, 13 Oct 2025), and legal review runs through EXTERNAL counsel that ARUP emails Word documents to, so Zycus paper will route to outside counsel, a step nothing has pre-aligned. With the proposal due 10 Jul and close 31 Jul only ~21 days remain. Pre-staging the MSA/SOW plus InfoSec and the external-counsel redline path now is what protects the date."}, "economic_buyer": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Zycus Debrief 16 Oct 2025", "Catch up with Zycus 09 Jan 2026"], "narrative": "Budget authority sits with a director referred to on calls only as 'mister Bevan' who mandated the Conga gap analysis and, per Michael, questioned buying the AI module standalone ('can I get the AI module without buying anything else' - 16 Oct 2025). He has never appeared on a Zycus call and is not in the Salesforce contact roles, so his exact name and title are unconfirmed from the relevant stakeholder this champion-authored tender the path to him runs THROUGH Michael Tutton, not around him: arming the champion with a leadership-facing value and ROI narrative is the move, not cold outreach to an unverified contact."}, "decision_process": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Catch up with Zycus 09 Jan 2026", "Call with Michael Tutton 04 Feb 2026", "SF Next_Step 6/29", "Task 2026-06-24 (Mzia Sturua)"], "narrative": "Well mapped from the call sequence: champion-led internal selling, repeated CLM demos, a Bevan-mandated Conga-vs-Zycus gap analysis run with the Salesforce/Conga team over several rounds (Oct 2025 to Feb 2026), an internal executive summary Michael built, and now a formal competitive RFP that is live with multiple suppliers (Mzia Sturua, 24 Jun 2026: 'we are sharing the responses to submitted questions with all suppliers'). The RFP is both a competitive bid and a political compromise letting the director validate the champion objectively. The post-proposal selection and award timeline is the critical unknown."}, "decision_criteria": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Zycus X ARUP CLM Demo 13 Oct 2025", "Zycus Debrief 16 Oct 2025", "SF Next_Step 6/29"], "narrative": "Criteria are clear and now codified in the RFP against Conga's gap set: side-by-side compare and redlining, clause and template library, restricted clause-level editing, external-counsel Word collaboration without portal login, AI contract discovery and Insta-review risk scoring, post-contract obligation and utilization dashboards, and D365/Merlin integration. On 13 Oct 2025 Robert Stipanovich probed licensing for external counsel and suppliers and Ondraya Watkins probed supplier risk scoring, showing the evaluation is criteria-led. The stated bar is explicitly what Conga cannot do."}}}